					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Sasha Han</h4>
												<p>Sasha Han is interested in the circulation of images in Southeast Asia and its potential for resistance. Her writing has been published by the Asian Film Archive, Documentary Magazine, Film Comment, MARG1N Magazine, Mekong Review and MUBI Notebook. She has presented underground film programmes in Singapore, at Festival Film Dokumenter, and has been part of the pre-selection team at the Singapore International Film Festival since 2022. In 2025, she co-founded Correspondence, a guerilla film publication centred on Southeast Asian films based in Singapore. Her work can be found here: sashahan.com</p>
